### Product Catalog API - Test Examples
### NOTE: Requires dotnet run to be executed first
### Base URL: http://localhost:5000

### IMPORTANT FLOW #1: CREATE A NEW PRODUCT
### This tests the CREATE flow (INSERT into database)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Gaming Laptop",
  "description": "High-performance laptop for gaming",
  "price": 1299.99,
  "stockQuantity": 15,
  "category": "Electronics"
}

### IMPORTANT FLOW #2: CREATE SECOND PRODUCT
POST http://localhost:5000/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Wireless Mouse",
  "description": "Ergonomic wireless mouse",
  "price": 49.99,
  "stockQuantity": 50,
  "category": "Accessories"
}

### IMPORTANT FLOW #3: GET ALL PRODUCTS
### This tests the READ ALL flow (SELECT * with filtering)
### Should return both products you just created
GET http://localhost:5000/api/products

### IMPORTANT FLOW #4: GET SINGLE PRODUCT BY ID
### Replace 1 with actual product ID from create response
GET http://localhost:5000/api/products/1

### IMPORTANT FLOW #5: GET PRODUCTS BY CATEGORY
### Filters products by category name (uses index for performance)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/products/category/Electronics

### IMPORTANT FLOW #6: UPDATE A PRODUCT
### Updates existing product (changes name and price)
### ID must exist in database
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/products/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Gaming Laptop Pro",
  "description": "Updated description with better specs",
  "price": 1399.99,
  "stockQuantity": 20,
  "category": "Electronics"
}

### IMPORTANT FLOW #7: UPDATE PRODUCT STOCK
### Uses PATCH to adjust inventory (positive = add, negative = remove)
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/products/1/stock
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "quantityAdjustment": 5
}

### IMPORTANT FLOW #8: DELETE A PRODUCT (SOFT DELETE)
### Marks product as inactive (data preserved in database)
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/products/1

### Additional Test Cases

### Test: Create product with invalid price
POST http://localhost:5000/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Invalid Product",
  "description": "Price is zero",
  "price": 0,
  "stockQuantity": 10,
  "category": "Test"
}

### Test: Get non-existent product
GET http://localhost:5000/api/products/999

### Test: Get products by category (no results expected)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/products/category/NonExistent
